# pear-end.bundle (and the throwaway ios-spike.bundle) are bare-bundle's
# fixed-byte-offset binary container format. They contain zero NUL bytes,
# so git's own binary-detection heuristic misclassifies them as text and
# silently LF->CRLF-converts them on checkout under Windows' common
# core.autocrlf=true default -- corrupting every offset in the bundle
# header without any error, so it fails much later at JS-module-load time
# with a misleading "is not valid JSON" crash. Force binary explicitly.
*.bundle binary
